	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=41412><span id=Scholar>Easirok</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>25 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Haha! You have got to be joking!<br><br>Fact is that a warrior has to work extremely hard to protect his group, if thats what he thinks his job is. The -only- tools you have to control aggro are that silly taunt button and (post 50) your Defensive discipline. So what if you have higher AC and hitpoints! That doesnt make you any better at controlling aggro. At level 56, a paladin is only about 100ac and 500hp behind a warrior on average. Thats only 5 hits from an average encounter mob, or 1-2 from a raid mob.<br><br>You will be in for a rude awakening once you hit level 50 and find out that the pally next to you has to -stop hitting- the mob, just so you can keep your aggro up. He will be doing nearly the same damage as you, possibly more, will likely be stunning to control casters, and quite often doing backup healing for the primary healer(s). And have you ever seen the cleric or enchanter in your group's health meter go from 10% to 100% instantly? Thats a LoH buddy, and it just saved your whole group.<br><br>Keep playing your warrior as a meat sheild, as thats what he is really for, but dont get caught up in the baseless opinion that a warrior is a protective class and a paladin is worthless because you see them die often. When a pally dies its usually because of either 1) they just used LoH on someone with high aggro, basically a sacrifice to save the cleric/chanter, or 2) they are still not very skilled in controlling their own innate taunt level.<br><br>If you doubt what I say about the damage ability or a paladin and his ability to keep himself alive, then I challenge you to duel one sometime. I would put my bets on the pally spanking you. He may not even need to use more than a couple casts or his LoH to do it either.<br><br>And speaking of the item in question here... it is one marvelous peice of gear. The ac alone on it is more than many breastplates. The +str/wis/hp are very welcome by a paladin. And the +5 to all saves is remarkable. Although I currently use a 2H peircer, I would gladly trade up my Trueheart sheild for this, and would likely stop using my peircer.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
