	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 19th 2:38 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=111693><span id= >Tall</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Easirok, on some points I agree and others I disagree.<br><br>As it stands right now, the only viable tank for your velious-style uber-mob is a defensive warrior. Your typical guild killing ubermobs probably has their warriors riding at 5200-5700'ish? hp or so. They're absolutely efficient and can be replaced by no other. You question their aggro ability. Well...<br><br>As it stands and from MUCH experience with mobs of all types (easy sh*t, mid to high level sh*t, and uber mobs 60+), Shadowknight taunt &gt; Paladin taunt &gt; Warrior taunt. Why is that? Spells. You will NOT out-taunt a Warrior in PURE melee as a Paladin or Shadowknight. HOWEVER, the main tank of my guild is a level 60 Shadowknight. He can hold a mob on him like it's glued to him. Shadowknight spells cause aggro even when resisted (to some extent). Using a combo of certain spells, taunting for him is no problem. For me, a 59 Paladin, I've found I'm also quite capable of taunting many mobs with similar ease, but not quite as well as the Shadowknight. Your typical 60+ mob that is Tash and Malo-able, I can taunt fine. <br><br>This Shadowknight and Paladin taunting has its advantages. Enchanters, Shamans, and whoever else can immediately cast necessary spells as the pull is incoming because of the solid aggro on the main tank.<br><br>Disadvantages? With your common mid-to-high level gear, racial and class differences, our Shadowknight tanks and me (Paladin) have a few hundred hp less than our 60 Warrior(s) (assuming equivalent gear), and depending on who, a bit less AC. The main thing that sets us apart is lack of Defensive. My what a beautiful discipline. We simply lack the damage mitigation to viably tank an uber mob (in most cases). This is where the warriors are alone. On the note of getting aggro, their usual 10-15 second pretaunt and decent weapons (epics, willsapper, etc) can allow them to hold aggro plenty well throughout the fight.<br><br>Paladin/Shadowknight? Sacrifice some HP/AC for guaranteed taunting. Warrior? More HP/AC for slightly shakey taunt, but can become solid given a pre-taunt period, and the eternally-used Defensive discipline.<br><br>I DO agree with you on one point for sure, Paladins and Shadowknights are far from useless. On your uberguild-level raids, what is my role? DS bitch (when I reach 60) and LoH a puller, yep.<br>Shadowknight? Not sure. Only viable tank (picture North ToV): Warrior.<br><br>East/West Wing in ToV type mobs? We almost ALWAYS have Shadowknights (sometimes me) tanking. The extent of melee damage our hybrid tanks endure is typically quad 330's. (On a side note, our main-tank 60 Shadowknight has tanked Bazzt Zzzt [quad 850's], Noble Dojorn [quad 750's], and other various high-hitting mobs, but those are a few exceptions). Personally, I find it insanely efficient and quick to use hybrid (usually SK's) to tank mobs of this caliber. Speed, ease of 1-person-getting-hit, and everyone else can jump right in (rogues, enchanters, shamans) without fear of getting beat up.<br><br>Typical pick-up group in Sebilis? Hybrid all the way. This is where Shadowknights and Paladins own. Few things in that zone resist; it's solid taunting and a breeze of killing.<br><br>So?<br><br>Uber-mobs: Warriors<br>Mid-uber-mobs: hybrids<br>Pick-up groups: hybrids<br><br>Are we useless? Not really. Don't ever doubt the tanking power of a Warrior either, though.<br><br>On the side note of "At level 56, a paladin is only about 100ac and 500hp behind a warrior on average. Thats only 5 hits from an average encounter mob, or 1-2 from a raid mob."<br><br>Every single HP matters. When you're main tanking mid-to-high hitting mobs, you're going to receives Complete Heals. Every single HP more you have makes each CH you receive just that much more efficient. <br><br>an ancient frost guardian claws YOU for 330 points of damage.<br><br>You see that and think 100hp is nothing, this mob hits for over 3 times this! Wrong!<br><br><br>Okay I think I'm done now...</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>59 Knight of Xegony</td></tr>
